                <h1>Capturing the Truth: Understanding Crime Scene Photos</h1>
                <p>Crime scene photos serve as vital evidence in criminal investigations, capturing details that may otherwise fade over time. They provide a visual account of the scene, aiding detectives in piecing together events leading up to a crime. However, their sensitive nature necessitates ethical considerations regarding privacy and respect for victims.</p>
